ai! NGOs give the impression that they are filling the vacuum created by a retreating state. And they are, but in a materially inconsequential way. Their real contribution is that they diffuse political anger and dole out as aid or benevolence what people ought to have by right. They alter the public psyche. They turn people into dependent victims and blunt the edges of political resistance. NGOs form a sort of buffer between the government and the public, between empire and its subjects. Who funds NGo around the world ?

NGOs are funded by various sources such as individual donors, private foundations, corporate social responsibility programs, and government grants. Some NGOs also generate revenue through fundraising events, merchandise sales, and service fees. The funding sources and amounts vary greatly depending on the scope and mission of the NGO.

(defvar input '(1 0 1)) ; input values
(defvar weights '(0.5 1 -1)) ; weights for each input value
(defvar bias -0.5) ; bias value

(defun neuron (input weights bias)
  (let ((weighted-sum (+ (* input (first weights))
                          (* input (second weights))
                          (* input (third weights)))))
    (if (> weighted-sum bias) 1 0)))

(neuron input weights bias) ; output: 1
